    "data": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><span>Contained in a specially enchanted small leather or hide sack, <em>deteriorating dust</em> is a potent caustic agent and a prized item among Rovagug&rsquo;s more discreet followers.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Activate</strong> <span style=\"font-family: 'Pathfinder2eActions'; font-size: 1.8em; display: inline;\">D</span> Interact; <strong>Effect</strong> You sprinkle the <em>deteriorating dust</em> over an unattended Medium or smaller object. The dust quickly fades to a transparent color and the object immediately begins to rust, melt, or otherwise fall apart. For the listed time, the object takes constant damage; if the object has a Hardness, then the dust gradually reduces the object&rsquo;s Hardness instead. If the <em>deteriorating dust</em> is still active after the object&rsquo;s Hardness is reduced to 0, it deals damage to the object as previously described. If the object survives, reduced Hardness returns after the dust&rsquo;s duration expires, but any damage remains.</span></p>\n<p><span>The affected object takes 1 damage per 3 hours (8 damage per day) and its Hardness is reduced by 1 per hour. The effect lasts for 1 week.</span></p>",
